on the right is the
bigger of the pair?

02:11:41.660 --> 02:11:43.900
Oh, wow. So this one
was much more split.

02:11:43.900 --> 02:11:47.930
So the image on the left
is actually stars dying

02:11:47.930 --> 02:11:51.460
because that's my favorite
in the Small Magellanic Cloud

02:11:51.460 --> 02:11:54.460
which is a really small
satellite mini-galaxy not too

02:11:54.460 --> 02:11:56.960
far away from us but still,
it's like, I don't know,

02:11:56.960 --> 02:11:58.750
100,000 light years away.

02:11:58.750 --> 02:12:05.800
And then the image on its right
is Mycobacterium tuberculosis.

02:12:05.800 --> 02:12:08.060
And when you look at
these images up close,

02:12:08.060 --> 02:12:10.110
I don't know how
great your view is.

02:12:10.110 --> 02:12:13.110
The visual resemblance
between the two is really

02:12:13.110 --> 02:12:14.440
quite striking.

02:12:14.440 --> 02:12:18.780
So the fact that we are able to
look at this from a microscope

02:12:18.780 --> 02:12:20.700
for the one on the right and
through a telescope for the one

02:12:20.700 --> 02:12:22.710
on the left is absolutely
incredible.

02:12:22.710 --> 02:12:25.130
I'll just do the other pairs
really quickly for people

02:12:25.130 --> 02:12:27.460
who want to finish
the game on their own.

02:12:27.460 --> 02:12:31.070
Pair two is the sun
compared with Raji cells.

02:12:31.070 --> 02:12:34.380
And those Raji cells can lead
to Epstein Barr syndrome.

02:12:34.380 --> 02:12:38.210
Pair three, onion cells and
another dead star, my favorite.

02:12:38.210 --> 02:12:40.940
So that's the ones here
on the bottom left.

02:12:40.940 --> 02:12:44.750
Pair four is rabbit tongue
cells compared to Jupiter

02:12:44.750 --> 02:12:46.840
so that's the upper right.

02:12:46.840 --> 02:12:49.670
And the one underneath it is
a comparison between Mercury,

02:12:49.670 --> 02:12:52.600
our planet and embryonic
